Very tolerant of proxies personally. Someones budget should effect our games.

I’m less enthused about them precisely because of budget, actually. I haven’t raised the issue, but there’s a dude in my group who has proxied out the majority of one of his decks. It’s been six months; there’s no intention of actual acquisition for those cards. Seems kinda dumb since there are budget players in the group who don’t play with fake cards and make do with what they have. 

Also, proxies don’t help you learn what you need to learn at the pace you have to learn it. So that’s a thing. Minor, but still a thing.

I agree. If you can’t afford “the best” work to find an alternative. The game allows that and perhaps you’ll find something that works better for you. The whole point of EDH isn’t to solve it and play the beat version of any deck.
That annoyance has hit me once, but mostly because he proxied out a deck, claimed it was casual... then burnt everyone with prosh combo. That made everyone pretty salty on that person for a while.
If you proxy to keep up, cool. If you proxy to try and stomp everyone though... I'm sure theres a ring of hell specially for those people
It’s not like you can’t do degenerate things on a budget in EDH
True. Number one edh deck in tappedout was the 25 dollar mikaeous deck
... which outgrew itself when mikaeous became over 25 himself
